node.text: We brought a burst of Icelandic adrenaline to London last weekend 🌋🔥 On the evening of Friday 11th June, we projected the Fagradalsfjall volcano eruption onto The National Gallery, The Senate House Library and the BBC building for Londoners to get their own taste of fiery Icelandic adventure! Want to see how it all happened? Watch this video, and let us know if our stunt has stoked the flames for Icelandic adventure to be #AroundTheCorner for you?

node.text:
Today we mark our support of equality by dedicating flight FI528/529 between Keflavík and Berlin to the visibility of the LGBTQ+ community. The cabin crew and pilots on our "Pride Flight" are all proud supporters of the LGBTQ+ community. The service on board is themed accordingly – we serve treats, rainbows, and a festive mood 🏳️‍🌈

node.text:
"GARÐAR BA 64. The whaler was built in Norway in 1912 (the year of the Titanic disaster) making it the oldest steal boat in Iceland. After serving its time out at sea it was stranded by its captain in 1981 where it had stayed since, decorating the beautiful Skápadalur valley."

Credits: @thrainnko

#MyStopover

node.text:
🌋Lockdown has left us hungry for adventure. In Iceland, that much-needed shot of adrenaline is always #AroundTheCorner. That's why we want to give 2 lucky adventurers and their loved ones the trip of a 'post-lockdown' lifetime.

🤳Tell us who you would bring in the comments below, and why you both deserve 'post-lockdown' adventure, or tag us in a selfie in front of one of our projections in London tonight (11 June) using #AroundTheCorner on your story. You could be on your way to Iceland to visit the Blue Lagoon and Fagradalsfjall volcano - but that's not all: there's also 10 gift certificates worth £400 each that can be used on return flights to Iceland. 

📅This competition closes 4pm on 16 June 2021. UK residents only (18+) can enter (see T&Cs on the Icelandair Facebook page).
